                            </path>
                        </svg></span>How does Air Tutor work?</h3>
                <span class="answer" id="answer7">First, the student makes a request asking for help with their
                    homework.
                    This can be done on the Request page. This request is sent to the Posts page, which is a list of
                    requests made by students.<br><br>
                    When the tutor browses the Posts page, they can message the student. The
                    student then schedules a meeting and decides the payment. At the time of the session, the tutor
                    begins the session where the student can join. During the session, they are able to use our voice
                    calling and canvas functions in order to communicate and learn better.<br><br>
                    After the session is over,
                    the student rates the teacher based on whether or not they were able to answer the question. This
                    rating will be later averaged on the tutor's profile, which will be helpful for the tutor's future
                    students to see.</span>
            </div>
